# Sound Level Meter

## Overview
This repository contains a simple Sound Level Meter application that uses a microphone to capture sound levels and display them in real-time using a bar chart. The application also allows you to set a maximum sound level threshold.

## Technologies Used
- HTML5
- JavaScript
- Chart.js library
- chartjs-plugin-annotation library

## Features
- Captures real-time sound levels from the microphone.
- Displays the sound level in a bar chart.
- Allows you to set a maximum sound level threshold via a spinner control.
- Changes the background color of the canvas if the sound level exceeds the set threshold.

## How to Use
1. Open `index.html` in a web browser.
2. Click the "Start Microphone" button to start capturing sound.
3. Use the spinner control to set the maximum sound level threshold.

